{
  "id": "vscode_cpp_cmake_workspace",
  "app": "vscode",
  "task": "Create a C++ CMake project at `/home/user/projects/cpp-calc` with the following files:\n\n- `main.cpp`:\n  ```cpp\n  #include <iostream>\n  #include \"calc.h\"\n  int main() {\n      std::cout << add(2, 3) << std::endl;\n      return 0;\n  }\n  ```\n- `calc.h`:\n  ```cpp\n  #pragma once\n  int add(int a, int b);\n  int subtract(int a, int b);\n  ```\n- `calc.cpp`:\n  ```cpp\n  #include \"calc.h\"\n  int add(int a, int b) { return a + b; }\n  int subtract(int a, int b) { return a - b; }\n  ```\n- `CMakeLists.txt`:\n  ```\n  cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.10)\n  project(cpp-calc)\n  set(CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD 17)\n  add_executable(cpp-calc main.cpp calc.cpp)\n  ```\n- `.vscode/tasks.json` — a shell task labeled `CMake Build` running `cmake -B build && cmake --build build`.\n- `.vscode/launch.json` — a `cppdbg` configuration named `Debug Calc` that runs the built binary from the `build` directory.\n- `.vscode/extensions.json` — recommends `ms-vscode.cpptools` and `twxs.cmake`.",
  "env": {
    "files": []
  },
